<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-23T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="607" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/871: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-23T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 23,
                                        1922—11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>295. Your 494, December 14:4 P.M.</p>
                        <p>Your recommendations concerning the method for making indemnity payments
                            are approved. It is assumed that you intend the retained portion shall
                            be paid into the International Banking Corporation for transmission to
                            the Treasury and that the remitted <pb facs="0936" n="816" xml:id="pg_816"/> portion shall continue to be paid by the Inspector
                            General to the Foreign Office in accordance with the Legation’s despatch
                            No. 1838 of December 31, 1917.<note n="88" xml:id="d607fn88">Figures as
                                on original document.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>